    "slug": "we-live-our-lives-from-the-inside-from-the-vantage-point-of-our-own-personal",
    "texto": "we live our lives from the \"inside\", from the vantage point of our own personal mini-cam on life. This gives us privileged access to what's going on inside our own heads. But sometimes we can be too close to ourselves to see us as we truly are. We lack perspective, objectivity. That's where friends can help. Friends can tell you when you're selfish or rude or making a total fool of yourself. Conversely, they can let you know when you're being kind or generous or need to lighten up on yourself.",
